title: 7 English words in Here Comes The Sun: Learn English with The Beatles

json.text: What's up
Guys this video is going to have seven English vocabulary words from the Beatles song, Here comes the Sun
Plus one bonus word that no teacher will ever teach you in English class. Thanks for watching
The first vocabulary word I want to bring up is
Darling, and this is kind of an old-fashioned word and it's a name for someone you love other words that have the same
meaning are
Dear honey, and sweetie. Now, this word is not that common anymore
It's kind of old-fashioned, but you still hear it from time to time in movies and songs
Lonely this word means alone and this is a sad word
It means you don't have any friends or anyone to talk to
Smile, this is the face that you make when you're happy like this
Return this means to come back
It's when something used to be here, and then went away and then
Returned or came back again
Slowly, this is when something is not happening
Fast it's happening slowly
Melting this is what happens when you have some ice, but the temperature is hot so your ice turns into water
Clear this word means see-through as in you can see through it
Like a window, but we can also use this word to say that the weather is nice
This is a picture of a clear day. This is not a picture of a clear day
See how you can't see through the fog because it's not clear and what does he mean when he's saying?
Doo-doo-doo-doo well in this case it doesn't mean anything. It's just noise
But there is a word called doodoo and it means poop
Now this this is a slang word
So you will never hear this word taught in an English class
But you will hear it from time to time
In movies and TV shows so thanks for watching my video be sure to keep listening to the song and practicing your English
If you have any questions about this song you can ask them in the comments below
